<h3> Psychtoolbox-3 </h3>

<br />
Psychophysics Toolbox Version 3 (PTB-3) is a free set of <a class="ext" href="http://www.mathworks.com">Matlab</a> and <a class="ext" href="http://www.octave.org">GNU/Octave</a> functions for vision research. It makes it easy to synthesize and show accurately controlled visual and auditory stimuli and interact with the observer.  It has at least fifteen thousand active users (see <a class="" href="http://psychtoolbox.org/wikka.php?wakka=PsychtoolboxOverview">Overview</a>), an active <a class="" href="http://psychtoolbox.org/wikka.php?wakka=PsychtoolboxForum">forum</a>, and is highly <a class="" href="http://psychtoolbox.org/PTB-3/citations.html">cited</a>. PTB-3 is based on the Psychophysics Toolbox Version 2 (PTB-2) but its Matlab extensions (in C) were rewritten to be more modular and use OpenGL. This Wiki describes the current version (PTB-3), which runs with Matlab 7.x and Octave 3.2.x on Mac OSX, Linux and Windows  (see <a class="" href="http://psychtoolbox.org/wikka.php?wakka=SystemRequirements">System Requirements</a>). The old PTB-2, for Mac OS 9 and Windows, still used in many labs, remains <a class="" href="http://psychtoolbox.org/PTB-2/">available</a> but is no longer developed or supported.<br />
